@node 0. "Introduction"

        Rand is a program that will perform randomly selected actions for
you.  For example, it can perform an operation on a randomly selected file,
or it can run a randomly selected program, or it can run a program with
randomly selected arguments. It is quite useful at boot time.  It can
select random backdrops, pointers, background patterns, screen blankers,
default icons, etc.  And its uses don't end there.  It could be used to
display random pictures, to play random modules, to display random quips to
the screen, etc.  And don't let my imagination stop you.  You might be able
to find other uses for it.

@endnode

@node 1. "Copyright"

        Rand v1.00 Copyright © 1995 @{"Fergus Duniho" link 7.}

        Rand is freeware.  If you feel a need to reward me for this useful
gem of a program, just let me know how useful and indispensible it is to
you.

@endnode

